{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_38","type":"agent_message","text":"接下來我會做這個實作切分，先走測試再補程式碼：  \n1. 新增 `clipboard_paste.rs` 與 `image_placeholders.rs`，先寫單元測試（placeholder 解析、多圖檔讀取、媒體類型判斷、錯誤情境）。  \n2. 在 `tui.rs` 增加 Ctrl+V 分支：成功插入 `@image:<tmp_path>`，失敗寫入 inline status error。  \n3. 將 TUI/agent/repl 送出前都走同一個 placeholder parser，產生 `Vec<ImageSource>` 丟進 `run_with_metrics`。  \n4. 接上 clipboard image pipeline（`arboard` file list 優先、fallback `get_image`、`image-process`、`tempfile`）。  \n5. 跑 fmt/clippy/test，最後 commit 指定訊息。  \n հիմա先開始加測試與新模組骨架。"}}
{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_39","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"cat > /tmp/us013_image_placeholders.rs <<'EOF'\nuse ccode_domain::llm::{ImageData, ImageMediaType, ImageSource};\n\n#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]\npub enum ImagePlaceholderError {\n    #[error(\\\"not implemented\\\")]\n    NotImplemented,\n}\n\npub fn load_images_from_placeholders(_input: &str) -> Result<Vec<ImageSource>, ImagePlaceholderError> {\n    Err(ImagePlaceholderError::NotImplemented)\n}\n\npub fn collect_image_placeholder_paths(_input: &str) -> Vec<String> {\n    Vec::new()\n}\n\npub fn media_type_from_path(_path: &std::path::Path) -> Result<ImageMediaType, ImagePlaceholderError> {\n    Err(ImagePlaceholderError::NotImplemented)\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n    use base64::Engine;\n    use tempfile::TempDir;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn collects_all_image_placeholders_in_message() {\n        let input = \\\"look @image:/tmp/a.png and @image:/tmp/b.jpg\\\\n@image:/tmp/c.webp\\\";\n        let paths = collect_image_placeholder_paths(input);\n        assert_eq\"'!(paths, vec![\"/tmp/a.png\", \"/tmp/b.jpg\", \"/tmp/c.webp\"]);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn resolves_placeholders_to_base64_images() {\n        let tmp = TempDir::new().expect(\"tempdir\");\n        let png_path = tmp.path().join(\"a.png\");\n        let gif_path = tmp.path().join(\"b.gif\");\n        std::fs::write(&png_path, b\"png-bytes\").expect(\"write png\");\n        std::fs::write(&gif_path, b\"gif-bytes\").expect(\"write gif\");\n\n        let input = format!(\n            \"hello @image:{} world @image:{}\",\n            png_path.display(),\n            gif_path.display()\n        );\n\n        let images = load_images_from_placeholders(&input).expect(\"parse images\");\n        assert_eq!(images.len(), 2);\n\n        assert_eq!(images[0].media_type, ImageMediaType::Png);\n        assert_eq!(images[1].media_type, ImageMediaType::Gif);\n\n        let decoded0 = base64::engine::general_purpose::STANDARD\n            .decode(match &images[0].data {\n                ImageData::Base64(v) => v,\n                ImageData::Url(_) => panic!(\"expected base64\"),\n            })\n            .expect(\"decode0\");\n        assert_eq!(decoded0, b\"png-bytes\");\n\n        let decoded1 = base64::engine::general_purpose::STANDARD\n            .decode(match &images[1].data {\n                ImageData::Base64(v) => v,\n                ImageData::Url(_) => panic!(\"expected base64\"),\n            })\n            .expect(\"decode1\");\n        assert_eq!(decoded1, b\"gif-bytes\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn rejects_unsupported_extension() {\n        let tmp = TempDir::new().expect(\"tempdir\");\n        let path = tmp.path().join(\"a.bmp\");\n        std::fs::write(&path, b\"bmp\").expect(\"write\");\n\n        let input = format!(\"@image:{}\", path.display());\n        let err = load_images_from_placeholders(&input).expect_err(\"should fail\");\n        assert!(err.to_string().contains(\"unsupported image extension\"));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn missing_image_file_returns_error() {\n        let input = \"@image:/tmp/does-not-exist.png\";\n        let err = load_images_from_placeholders(input).expect_err(\"should fail\");\n        assert!(err.to_string().contains(\"failed to read image file\"));\n    }\n}\nEOF\n\ncat > /tmp/us013_clipboard_paste.rs <<'\"'EOF'\n#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]\npub enum ClipboardPasteError {\n    #[error(\\\"not implemented\\\")]\n    NotImplemented,\n}\n\npub fn paste_image_from_clipboard_to_temp_file() -> Result<std::path::PathBuf, ClipboardPasteError> {\n    Err(ClipboardPasteError::NotImplemented)\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn placeholder() {\n        let err = paste_image_from_clipboard_to_temp_file().expect_err(\\\"unimplemented\\\");\n        assert\"'!(err.to_string().contains(\"not implemented\"));\n    }\n}\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
